               <head>Ghazipur, biographical history</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary/>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/n85141803 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008114816 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2005005467 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008115920 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85053991" n="1" xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_4084-item1">
                     <note>
                        <p>Author and title not stated in work</p>
                        <p>Alternative title on label attached to covers (deleted by William Irvine): Tarikh Badshahan Delhi aur Nowaban Oudh</p>
                        <p>Alternative title on label attached to covers (most likely added by William Irvine): Account of Sayyad Masud &amp; of Shekh Abdullah &amp; Fazl Ali of [Oudh (?)]</p>
                        <p>Anonymous collection of biographical notices for notable persons, adminstrators and élites relating to the area of Ghāzīpūr (northwest of Varanasi, Uttar Pradesh State), beginning with the town's foundation by Amīr Sayyid Masʿūd Ghāzī (d. 767 / 1365-6), in 730 / 1329-30, and extending to the time of Navvāb ʿAlī ʿAẓīm Khān ibn Shaykh ʿAbd Allāh (d. 1222 / 1807-8)</p>
                        <p>The narrative is organised into a series of maṭlab and fuṣūl chapters, but without the addition of a preface to explain the work and its organisation</p>
                        <p>Not dated</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" xml:lang="per">Persian</textLang>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
